<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="https://1.bp.blogspot.com/-9BtTFWIfvXY/WHUSj1lhW-I/AAAAAAAALbU/rQWaAu9eZ7M_q5YsHwYqQn0KaYce9VLtwCLcB/s1600/AP1100132.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="clear: left; float: left; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="440" src="https://1.bp.blogspot.com/-9BtTFWIfvXY/WHUSj1lhW-I/AAAAAAAALbU/rQWaAu9eZ7M_q5YsHwYqQn0KaYce9VLtwCLcB/s640/AP1100132.jpg" width="640" /></a></div>I can't think that anyone would chose to climb in the rain but we've made the most of a wet second day of the <a href="http://www.expeditionguide.com/wintermountaineering.php">Scottish Winter Mountaineering Course</a> climbing the ever popular <i>Dorsal Arete</i> in Glencoe's Stob Coire nan Lochan. Despite the drizzle it was of course still enjoyable and actually a good deal harder in gaining the 'fin' than I ever remember it being before. The absence of a depth of snow to reduce the stretch of a high step up must make all the difference. There was little however to commend the sloshing descent out of the corrie through fast thawing snow.&nbsp; A fireside seat in the Clachaig restored the good-bad balance. <br /><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="https://1.bp.blogspot.com/-lChOMlW46sk/WHUSlqH1n9I/AAAAAAAALbY/gn2fSd6Gj0kwC2rqzWrGU2JreG9mHefrQCLcB/s1600/AP1100104.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="clear: left; float: left; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="392" src="https://1.bp.blogspot.com/-lChOMlW46sk/WHUSlqH1n9I/AAAAAAAALbY/gn2fSd6Gj0kwC2rqzWrGU2JreG9mHefrQCLcB/s640/AP1100104.jpg" width="640" /></a></div><br /><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="https://3.bp.blogspot.com/-QmRZePaSS3g/WHUSnHrj9FI/AAAAAAAALbc/urnL5eU72Qo9VUlpoP9snCZ0BkkH1SAwgCLcB/s1600/AP1100115.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="clear: left; float: left; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="474" src="https://3.bp.blogspot.com/-QmRZePaSS3g/WHUSnHrj9FI/AAAAAAAALbc/urnL5eU72Qo9VUlpoP9snCZ0BkkH1SAwgCLcB/s640/AP1100115.jpg" width="640" /></a></div><br /><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="https://2.bp.blogspot.com/-sd6etZd8GEc/WHUSnoUgmZI/AAAAAAAALbg/uuvDjC7pm9MtUsnoAd2PZWmL9iQ2nwnFwCLcB/s1600/AP1100143.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="clear: left; float: left; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="456" src="https://2.bp.blogspot.com/-sd6etZd8GEc/WHUSnoUgmZI/AAAAAAAALbg/uuvDjC7pm9MtUsnoAd2PZWmL9iQ2nwnFwCLcB/s640/AP1100143.jpg" width="640" /></a></div><br /><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="https://1.bp.blogspot.com/-BNeuhsDY-g8/WHUSou_ZFBI/AAAAAAAALbk/RPlGhv2dlYcL3jkWV-RFlM0Uu8RTvb8GACLcB/s1600/AP1100108.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="clear: left; float: left; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="460" src="https://1.bp.blogspot.com/-BNeuhsDY-g8/WHUSou_ZFBI/AAAAAAAALbk/RPlGhv2dlYcL3jkWV-RFlM0Uu8RTvb8GACLcB/s640/AP1100108.jpg" width="640" /></a></div><br />